    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="403"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.24/7–1846</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pawley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/> No. 78</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-18">July 18,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Acting Secretary of State transmits for the confidential information and
                    files of the Embassy copies of a note of even date to the Brazilian Embassy in
                    Washington and of Statement LL–8<note n="51" xml:id="d403fn51">Neither
                        printed.</note> showing charges made against the Government of Brazil during
                    the period from December 1, 1945 through February 28, 1945 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >1946</hi>], for defense material transferred to Brazil under the Lend-Lease
                    Agreement signed March 3, 1942.</p>
                <p>It will be noted that the amount of charges during the period under reference is
                    $796,037.79 and that charges through February 28, 1946 aggregate the grand total
                    of $183,959,349.81. Under the terms of the Agreement a payment of $11,666,666.66
                    is now due.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
